title: Kika, Republic of Buryatia
content:
Kika (Russian: Кика) is a rural locality (a settlement) in Pribaykalsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 508 as of 2010.[2] There are 10 streets.

Kika is located 48 km northeast of Turuntayevo (the district's administrative centre) by road. Turulevo is the nearest rural locality.[3]
